== About Me

I'm a second-year PhD student in the [https://www.essie.ufl.edu/civil-coastal-engineering Department of Civil and Costal Engineering], [http://www.ufl.edu/ University of Florid], , majoring in Transportation Engineering (Please find my lab [https://faculty.eng.ufl.edu/sermos-lab here]). I received my bachelor degree in Transportation Engineering from [https://en.swjtu.edu.cn/ Southwest Jiao Tong University], Chengdu, China, where I was advised by [https://faculty.swjtu.edu.cn/yanghongtai/en/index.htm Prof. Hongtai Yang]. Before joining UF, I was a visiting research assistant at [https://shanghai.nyu.edu/ New York University Shanghai], Shanghai, China from 2020 to 2021, where I was advised by [https://shanghai.nyu.edu/academics/faculty/directory/zhibin-chen Prof. Zhibin Chen].

My research mainly focuses on the applications of data science (e.g., data analytics and machine learning) on travel behavior and evacuation behavior.

== Education
- Ph.D. in Transportation Engineering, University of Florida, January 2021 -- present.
- B.E. in Transportation Engineering, Southwest Jiaotong University, September 2016 -- June 2020.

== Recent News

~~~
- *Sept. 27th 2022* I got three papers accpted for this year's TRB, see you in DC!
- *Sept. 15th 2022* I gave a presentation entitled "Optimizing Rural Demand-Responsive Transport Operations  for Medical Trips" at TRANSED: Mobility, Accessibility & Demand Response Transportation Conference.
- *July. 15th 2022* I gave two presentations entitled "Modeling and Interpreting Protective Action Decision-Making During Earthquakes Using Machine Learning" and "Forecasting Person Activity During the COVID-19 Pandemic: A Case Study of Clematis Street in West Palm Beach, Florida" at Natural Hazards Center Researchers Meeting!
